programme.title: The Explorers
programme.desc: Two determined innovators push their limits, risking all, in order to realise their dreams, are profiled. Pushing the limits of possibility challenges people who are willing to go beyond the visible horizon, no matter the risks. Documentary film-maker Jimmy Chin and XPRIZE creator Peter Diamandis are explorers who are always looking for a new frontier.

programme.title: Budapest
programme.desc: Magician Adam Trent discovers that Budapest, Hungary, has a light and dark side. Can his tricks work in both? The first stop of magician Adam Trent's European journey is the party city of Budapest, Hungary. Adam wants to see the things that the tourists don't, but walking on the dark side has its risks. Can Adam's magic get him out of a dangerous situation?

programme.title: Amazon High Tide
programme.desc: Ramón Navarro is a surfer brave enough to cross the Amazon jungle and find a secret wave spot. Big wave surfer Ramón Navarro is determined enough to cross the remote Amazon jungle in Brazil in search of a secret wave spot.

programme.title: Gully Life
programme.desc: A look at how a young rapper from Mumbai became one of the most sought-after musicians in India. The first-ever documentary on his life, Gully Life: The Story of Divine takes a look at how a young rapper from Mumbai became one of the most sought-after musicians in India, and a global superstar.

programme.title: Taking Shape
programme.desc: Danny MacAskill starts a perfomance programme with his rehab trainer, first in the gym, then on his bike. As he recovers from major back surgery, cyclist Danny MacAskill films a TV documentary about action sports athletes with one of his heroes, Guy Martin. Then work of rehab begins as he starts to plan his moves for the film project.

programme.title: Atari
programme.desc: Nolan Bushnell changes global entertainment with his invention of an electronic, monochrome square ball. Nolan Bushnell, a businessman with carnival barker charm and a touch for electronics, changes global entertainment with his creation of the video game Pong. He not only revolutionises how people play games, but becomes the father of Silicon Valley.

programme.title: Plaid
programme.desc: A pattern to unite the world, Kyle Ng travels from the United States to Scotland and Kenya looking for plaid. A pattern to unite the world, Kyle Ng dives into plaid's history. He visits Scotland, UK to see how tartan is part of a family's DNA, hangs with a low rider club in California, USA, and sees how the fabric is a part of tribal identity in Africa.

programme.title: Prepping for Panama
programme.desc: Parks Bonifay rounds up some friends for an epic wakeboarding adventure in Panama they’ll never forget. Parks Bonifay rounds up some friends for an epic wakeboarding adventure in Panama they’ll never forget. Before heading off to the airport, Brian Grubb and Steel Lafferty join Parks for one last wakeskating session.

programme.title: The Seaplane Escapade
programme.desc: After arriving in Nitro City, Panama, Parks Bonifray and crew go wakeboarding with a seaplane. After landing in Panama, Parks Bonifay, Brian Grubb, and Steel Lafferty prepare for a wakeboarding session with a seaplane. Later, Brian and pro wakeboarder Collin Harrington skydive from a seaplane – hanging from the pontoons on the way up.

programme.title: Rob Meets Julien Absalon
programme.desc: Rob Warner gets personal with the king of cross-country mountain biking, Julien Absalon. With five World Championships, two Olympic golds, and seven overall wins on the World Tour, Julien Absalon is the king of cross-country mountain biking. Rob Warner travels to France to hear from the man himself about preparing for his final season.

programme.title: VMax: No Straight Line
programme.sub-title: Beating the mountain bike speed record, again
programme.desc: Max Stöckl's quest to be the fastest man on a mountain bike takes him from Austria to the mountains of Chile. Markus 'Max' Stöckl has been setting speed downhill mountain bike records for over 20 years. Now, in his endless desire to go faster, he attempts to break his own World Record of 164.95kph on a desolate peak in Chile's Atacama Desert.

programme.title: Wee Day Out
programme.desc: Danny MacAskill tears around rural Scotland, setting out to capture the simple fun of a ride in the country. A relaxing day out in the Scottish countryside means something different for Danny MacAskill than it does for most people. With his signature trial riding style, Danny makes his way over hay bales, through forests and all along the rolling hills.

programme.title: The Flare
programme.sub-title: Finding their own place in skateboarding
programme.desc: Take a whimsical look at the life of skateboarding with a group of young men just trying to not fit in. A jock, an outcast, a rebel and a princess: this modern-day Breakfast Club tell their story a little differently. Take a whimsical look at the life of skateboarding with a group of young men just trying to not fit in.

programme.title: Pororoca
programme.desc: A group of surfers travel to a remote part of the Amazon in an attempt to ride a destructive tidal wave. On every new and full moon, an enormous tidal wave occurs along the lower Amazon. It's a tempting target for surfers despite the many dangers involved, and it offers few who brave it the longest continuous rides of their lives.

programme.title: ABC of... Surfing
programme.desc: Discover some facts and figures of surfing, from its origins to the spectacular adrenaline-fuelled present. Learn some facts and figures of surfing, from its origins to the spectacular adrenaline-fuelled present that so many can’t live without. Surfing is a way of life for those who are hooked on it, and once you watch this you might be hooked too.

programme.title: Gotad Ad Kiangan
programme.desc: The ancestral heritage of the Ifugao of the Philippines is preserved in their Gotad Ad Kiangan festival. Being between the ancient and the modern, the Ifugao people of the Philippines continue their Gotad Ad Kiangan festival to preserve their fading heritage. It's a celebration of singing, dancing, and racing that culminates in a wrestling tournament.

programme.title: The rise of VGM
programme.desc: Explore the origins of Japanese video game music and its influence on modern-day musicians. From humble beginnings to worldwide recognition, Japanese video game music has inspired a generation. Meet Junko Ozawa, developer of the 'Namco sound', and iconic Nintendo composer Hirokazu Tanaka.

programme.title: The Training Heats Up
programme.desc: The b-boys train for the upoming BC One in Moscow. Lilou receives bad news and makes a strategic choice. When he discovers he can't compete in the BC One in Moscow, Lilou helps a fellow b-boy in order to beat his rival Neguin. In Sao Paulo, Neguin trains with his friend Andre. Roxrite gets an offer to compete in Moscow for the only title he's never won.

programme.title: Lessons from the Edge
programme.desc: Ultra-runners Ryan Sandes and Ryno Griesel set out to run the Great Himalaya Trail in the fastest known time. South African ultra-runners, Ryan Sandes and Ryno Griesel set out on the adventure of a lifetime: to run the Great Himalaya Trail in the fastest known time – a total of 1,406km in 28 days.
